Moving on to the deployment mode segmentation, cloud-based solutions are emerging as the preferred choice for ambulatory healthcare organizations. The scalability, flexibility, and cost-effectiveness offered by cloud-based IT solutions are driving their adoption across the market. Healthcare providers are opting for cloud solutions to securely store and manage patient data while enabling seamless access from various locations. This shift towards cloud deployment signifies a broader trend within the healthcare industry to leverage technology for improved operational efficiency and data accessibility.

In terms of end-users, the ambulatory healthcare IT market caters to a diverse range of facilities including hospitals, clinics, ambulatory surgery centers, and diagnostic centers. While hospitals currently dominate the market share due to their extensive use of advanced IT solutions for patient management and electronic records, clinics and ambulatory surgery centers are also witnessing a surge in demand for IT solutions. These facilities are increasingly focusing on enhancing operational productivity and patient experiences through the adoption of innovative IT tools.

